column5: Anyone stayed here before and know how the fishing is in the area?  I'll be there Friday-Sunday if anyone wants to hook me up with some info it would be much appreciated.  Any tips are welcomed!  Thank you in advance.

The best tip I can give you for the area is to bring your camera! The lake in that area have been hit hard by acid rain... fishing opportunities are very limited... but the scenery up there is 2nd to none, so bring the camera, the hiking boots and have fun! If you have access to a boat, Baie Fine is the world's only freshwater fjord and a simply beautiful place to see. HH
i'm sure everyone here is itching to help you out.

There was a Killarney report on here not too long ago....can't remember who posted it....but the fishing has really rebounded over the last few years from what I've read and heard. The report on here from this past summer had lots and lots of smallies in it...
Thank you! I'll have to try searching with less keywords!
